**Task 3.2: Box Model Mastery**

**box-model-practice.html**

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Box Model Practice</title>

    <style>
        /* General page styling */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* Common style for all boxes */
        .box {
            width: 300px;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 5px solid black;
            margin: 20px;
        }

        /* Different colors for each box */
        .content {
            background-color: lightblue;
        }

        .padding {
            background-color: lightgreen;
        }

        .border {
            background-color: lightcoral;
        }

        .margin {
            background-color: khaki;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Box Model Practice</h1>

    <div class="box content">
        <h2>Content</h2>
        <p>The blue area is the content section.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box padding">
        <h2>Padding</h2>
        <p>The space inside the border is called padding.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box border">
        <h2>Border</h2>
        <p>The black line around the box is the border.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box margin">
        <h2>Margin</h2>
        <p>The space between boxes is called margin.</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>



